Oxidized LDL cholesterol is more likely to stick to blood vessel walls and form plaque, which can lead to atherosclerosis and heart disease. Vitamin D is important for bone health. The government agency that protects investors is now taking aim at the growing practice of companies buying up their own shares. The Securities and Exchange Commission said Tuesday it is looking at the use of stock buybacks, which have surged in the past decade. The agency said it will examine whether buybacks are being used to "prop up share prices" and whether the practice is being used to meet other companies' earnings targets.
